<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: PCX2SNES (somehow) incorectly generates palette colors]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15975&amp;p=196766#p196766"><![CDATA[
GIMP also has a Posterize function that, when set to 32 levels, gives you effectively 15-bit colour.  The &quot;Colorcube Analysis&quot; tool counts the number of colours in an image, so you can tell if you're over the limit even if you aren't using Indexed mode.  You can even save bitmaps in X1R5G5B5, eliminating the need for your custom SNES graphics tool to do <em>any</em> colour conversion (unless it's on a platform that can't read 15-bit bitmaps...).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6595">93143</a> — Sat May 27, 2017 11:22 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
